{{Infobox Website | name = AlloCiné | logo = | screenshot = Allociné logo.jpg | screenshot_size = 191px | caption = | url = [http://www.allocine.fr/ allocine.fr] | commercial = | type = Film | language = French | registration = | owner = [[FIMALAC]] | author = [[Jean David Blanc|Jean-David Blanc]] & Patrick Holzman<ref name="Screen Daily">{{cite web|url=http://www.screendaily.com/founders-quit-as-allocine-expands-online-ticketing/405046.article|title=Founders quit as AlloCine expands online ticketing|publisher=Screen Daily|date=16 February 2001|author=Patrick Frater|accessdate=18 October 2013}}</ref> | launch date = 1993 | current status = Active | revenue = | alexa = 979 (France: 29) [http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/allocine.fr] | slogan = | content license = }} '''AlloCiné''' ({{lang-en|'''ScreenRush'''}}) is a company which provides information on [[French cinema]], especially centering on novelties' promotion with DVD, Blu-ray and [[Video on demand|VOD]] information. The enterprise was founded as a telephonic communicator, and subsequently became an Internet portal site, which offers sufficient information by fast access and covers all movies that have been distributed in France. In 2005, it began covering television series.
AlloCiné was launched in 1993, before being purchased by [[Canal+]] in 2000 and [[Vivendi Universal]] in 2002. From June 2007 to 2013, it was under the ownership of Tiger Global, an American investment fund. Since July 2013, Allociné has been owned by [[FIMALAC]],<ref name="À propos d'Allociné">{{cite web|url=http://www.allocine.fr/service/apropos/|title=À propos d'Allociné|accessdate=30 September 2015}}</ref> a French [[holding company]]. The [[corporate headquarters]] is located on the [[Champs-Élysées]] in Paris.
